<subSubSection id="51A220EFA0683D19DAE2FF5F4EEDFE2A" pageId="13" pageNumber="502" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="19077364A0683D19DAE2FF5F4E67FEBF" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis id="2BCCAF76A0683D19DAE2FF5F4C49FF12" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">Remarks.</emphasis>
Prior to the present study, 
<taxonomicName id="DEB808E7A0683D19D858FF514FCAFF12" authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1866" box="[637,696,153,176]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pectinariidae" genus="Petta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="502" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2BCCAF76A0683D19D858FF514FCAFF12" box="[637,696,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">Petta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a genus comprising only four species. The 
<typeStatus id="C603CDC6A0683D19DED6FF504851FF12" box="[1267,1315,152,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">type</typeStatus>
species is known from off 
<collectingCountry id="61AF33F4A0683D19DB7CFF744CC7FF77" box="[345,437,188,213]" name="Sweden" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, and the other species were described from specimens collected as far apart as in the Caribbean and Gulf of 
<collectingCountry id="61AF33F4A0683D19DB8FFF174F70FF5A" box="[426,514,223,248]" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Kerguelen Islands and 
<collectingCountry id="61AF33F4A0683D19D93AFF174EE2FF5A" box="[799,912,223,248]" name="Indonesia" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
. Therefore, the present study brings the first record for species of this genus for the southern Atlantic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19077364A0683D19DAE2FEEF4EEDFE2A" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">
Although 
<taxonomicName id="DEB808E7A0683D19DB12FEE14C00FEE2" authorityName="Malmgren" authorityYear="1866" box="[311,370,297,320]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pectinariidae" genus="Petta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="502" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2BCCAF76A0683D19DB12FEE14C00FEE2" box="[311,370,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">Petta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has few valid species currently, in most cases they are known only from 
<typeStatus id="C603CDC6A0683D19DEB9FEE049BEFEE2" box="[1180,1228,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">type</typeStatus>
material, which in some cases is lost or in poor condition, and the descriptions do not include several important taxonomic characters. A revision of the genus is currently under preparation by Zhang 
<emphasis id="2BCCAF76A0683D19D942FEB94EEDFE2A" box="[871,927,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="502">et al.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
